All tests pass. Now let me review the fix one more time to make sure it's correct:

```kt
internal fun Duration.toDelayMillis(): Long = if (this > Duration.ZERO) {
    val millis = inWholeMilliseconds
    // For very large durations (where millis * 1_000_000 would overflow), sub-ms precision doesn't matter
    if (millis >= Long.MAX_VALUE / 1_000_000) {
        millis
    } else {
        val nanos = inWholeNanoseconds
        // If the duration has sub-millisecond components (nanos > millis * 1_000_000), round up.
        // For small durations (< 1ms), this ensures we return at least 1.
        // For larger durations with sub-ms components, we add 1 to round up.
        if (nanos > millis * 1_000_000) millis + 1 else millis.coerceAtLeast(1)
    }
} else 0
```

This correctly handles:
1. Durations with sub-millisecond components (rounds up)
2. Exact millisecond durations (returns the exact millis)
3. Very large durations (avoids overflow by returning millis directly)
4. Positive durations less than 1ms (returns at least 1)
5. Zero and negative durations (returns 0)

The fix is complete and all existing tests pass.

